  "title": "Service Engineer (Chiller)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Attend to customer enquiries and complaints, including on-site calls</li>\n  <li>Recommend preventive measures and provide prompt and effective resolution to technical problems</li>\n  <li>Assuage dissatisfied customers with prompt resolutions for any product or service issues</li>\n  <li>Provide guidance and technical assistance to service teams and sub-contractors on service assignments, testing and commissioning; verify and prepare payment to sub-contractors</li>\n  <li>Remain actively involved in the implementation of department strategies and initiatives such as service value-chain businesses</li>\n  <li>Update Service information system and follow up with all necessary paper work diligently, timely and accurately for smooth operation of the department</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br>\n<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Mechanical Engineering</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of technical experience with knowledge in air-conditioning, chiller, ACMV or HVAC systems<br>\nResourceful with good analytical and interpersonal skills</li>\n  <li>Strong communication skills</li>\n  <li>Good team player with ability to lead and multi-task</li>\n  <li>Possess Class 3 driving license will be an added advantage</li>\n</ul>",
